# Rocq project file for rule consolidation formal verification
#
# Verifies semantic equivalence of Ascent rule consolidation:
# N per-constructor rules â†’ 1 consolidated rule with inline match.
#
# Six consolidation areas proven equivalent:
#   1. Subterm Extraction      (for-match)
#   2. Auto-Variant Congruence (for-match + variant-index)
#   3. Equation Congruence     (pair-match)
#   4. Explicit Congruence     (variant-index rebuild)
#   5. Fold Triggers           (if-match boolean)
#   6. Fold Identities         (if-match boolean)
#
# Build:
#   coq_makefile -f _CoqProject -o CoqMakefile && make -f CoqMakefile
#
# With resource limits (recommended):
#   coq_makefile -f _CoqProject -o CoqMakefile && \
#   systemd-run --user --scope -p MemoryMax=16G -p CPUQuota=400% make -f CoqMakefile
#
# Prerequisites:
#   - Rocq 9.0+ (tested with 9.1.0)
#   - Standard library (included with Rocq)

# Compiler flags
-Q theories RuleConsolidation

# Source files (dependency order)
theories/Prelude.v
theories/DisjointPatterns.v
theories/RuleConsolidation.v
theories/VariantIndexRebuild.v
theories/AreaProofs.v
